text.tspan: Enemy always finds a beeline (shortest path)
to reach the gold. Your goal is to place towers
in enemy's path so that this beeline gets as long
as possible. That keeps enemy on the map longer
and makes it possible to be hunted down by towers
(Your goal is to get full red circles)

Towers serve not only to kill enemy but to
create obstructions in its path, so that it has
to travel longer to reach the gold and escape.
Obstructing enemy path is as important as killing it.
The Block tower gives you cheaper way to
create such obstructions. It costs half the amount
of resources that you need for Gun.
A Laser beam inflicts continuous damage
on the target. Hence effective on faster moving
targets like Sprinter. It costs more.
It's weak against shields, so try to place it after
the enemy has been attacked by Gun or Canon
Laser is smart too. It targets gold carrying enemy first
The towers can be upgraded to get more out of them.
Two upgrades are supported on all actively firing towers
The upgrade costs vary depending upon the tower type.
It's a matter of strategy to choose to spend resources on
upgrading existing towers versus building new ones
